
 * it implements circuit breaker,

 * is responsible for turning off safety when a service is not responding,

 * It is used to detect failures and encapsulates the logic of preventing a failure from constantly recurring,
 during maintenance, temporary external system failure or unexpected system difficulties,

 dashboard:

 * see the number of hosts in the cluster,

 * see the performance of requests,

 * see the number of requests,

 * see thread pool properties,

 * there is a lot of data, and it is important to not overreact on this,

 * turbine (from netflix) - allows us to see many server instances on one view
 - gets all informations from all clients and displays that on one view

 how to use:

 * enable hystrix dashboard - add this annotation @EnableHystrixDashboard